72std::string RTCCodecStatsIDFromMidDirectionAndPayload(const std::string& mid,
73 bool inbound,
74 uint32_t payload_type) {

77 sb << "RTCCodec_" << mid << (inbound ? "_Inbound_" : "_Outbound_")

164const char* CandidateTypeToRTCIceCandidateType(const std::string& type) {
165 if (type == cricket::LOCAL_PORT_TYPE)
166 return RTCIceCandidateType::kHost;
167 if (type == cricket::STUN_PORT_TYPE)
168 return RTCIceCandidateType::kSrflx;
169 if (type == cricket::PRFLX_PORT_TYPE)
170 return RTCIceCandidateType::kPrflx;
171 if (type == cricket::RELAY_PORT_TYPE)
172 return RTCIceCandidateType::kRelay;
173 RTC_NOTREACHED();
174 return nullptr;
175}

177const char* DataStateToRTCDataChannelState(
178 DataChannelInterface::DataState state) {
179 switch (state) {
180 case DataChannelInterface::kConnecting:
181 return RTCDataChannelState::kConnecting;
182 case DataChannelInterface::kOpen:
183 return RTCDataChannelState::kOpen;
184 case DataChannelInterface::kClosing:
185 return RTCDataChannelState::kClosing;
186 case DataChannelInterface::kClosed:
187 return RTCDataChannelState::kClosed;
188 default:
189 RTC_NOTREACHED();
190 return nullptr;
191 }
192}

194const char* IceCandidatePairStateToRTCStatsIceCandidatePairState(
195 cricket::IceCandidatePairState state) {
196 switch (state) {
197 case cricket::IceCandidatePairState::WAITING:
198 return RTCStatsIceCandidatePairState::kWaiting;
199 case cricket::IceCandidatePairState::IN_PROGRESS:
200 return RTCStatsIceCandidatePairState::kInProgress;
201 case cricket::IceCandidatePairState::SUCCEEDED:
202 return RTCStatsIceCandidatePairState::kSucceeded;
203 case cricket::IceCandidatePairState::FAILED:
204 return RTCStatsIceCandidatePairState::kFailed;
205 default:
206 RTC_NOTREACHED();
207 return nullptr;
208 }
209}

230const char* NetworkAdapterTypeToStatsType(rtc::AdapterType type) {
231 switch (type) {
232 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR:
233 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_2G:
234 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_3G:
235 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_4G:
236 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_5G:
237 return RTCNetworkType::kCellular;
238 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_ETHERNET:
239 return RTCNetworkType::kEthernet;
240 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_WIFI:
241 return RTCNetworkType::kWifi;
242 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_VPN:
243 return RTCNetworkType::kVpn;
244 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_UNKNOWN:
245 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_LOOPBACK:
246 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_ANY:
247 return RTCNetworkType::kUnknown;
248 }
249 RTC_NOTREACHED();
250 return nullptr;
251}

268double DoubleAudioLevelFromIntAudioLevel(int audio_level) {
269 RTC_DCHECK_GE(audio_level, 0);
270 RTC_DCHECK_LE(audio_level, 32767);
271 return audio_level / 32767.0;
272}

274std::unique_ptr<RTCCodecStats> CodecStatsFromRtpCodecParameters(
275 uint64_t timestamp_us,
276 const std::string& mid,
277 const std::string& transport_id,
278 bool inbound,
279 const RtpCodecParameters& codec_params) {
280 RTC_DCHECK_GE(codec_params.payload_type, 0);
281 RTC_DCHECK_LE(codec_params.payload_type, 127);
282 RTC_DCHECK(codec_params.clock_rate);
283 uint32_t payload_type = static_cast<uint32_t>(codec_params.payload_type);
284 std::unique_ptr<RTCCodecStats> codec_stats(new RTCCodecStats(
285 RTCCodecStatsIDFromMidDirectionAndPayload(mid, inbound, payload_type),
286 timestamp_us));
287 codec_stats->payload_type = payload_type;
288 codec_stats->mime_type = codec_params.mime_type();
289 if (codec_params.clock_rate) {
290 codec_stats->clock_rate = static_cast<uint32_t>(*codec_params.clock_rate);
291 }
292 if (codec_params.num_channels) {
293 codec_stats->channels = *codec_params.num_channels;
294 }
295
296 rtc::StringBuilder fmtp;
297 if (WriteFmtpParameters(codec_params.parameters, &fmtp)) {
298 codec_stats->sdp_fmtp_line = fmtp.Release();
299 }
300 codec_stats->transport_id = transport_id;
301 return codec_stats;
302}

311// Provides the media independent counters (both audio and video).
312void SetInboundRTPStreamStatsFromMediaReceiverInfo(
313 const cricket::MediaReceiverInfo& media_receiver_info,
314 RTCInboundRTPStreamStats* inbound_stats) {
315 RTC_DCHECK(inbound_stats);
316 inbound_stats->ssrc = media_receiver_info.ssrc();
317 inbound_stats->packets_received =
318 static_cast<uint32_t>(media_receiver_info.packets_rcvd);
319 inbound_stats->bytes_received =
320 static_cast<uint64_t>(media_receiver_info.payload_bytes_rcvd);
321 inbound_stats->header_bytes_received =
322 static_cast<uint64_t>(media_receiver_info.header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd);
323 inbound_stats->packets_lost =
324 static_cast<int32_t>(media_receiver_info.packets_lost);
325}

327std::unique_ptr<RTCInboundRTPStreamStats> CreateInboundAudioStreamStats(
328 const cricket::VoiceReceiverInfo& voice_receiver_info,
329 const std::string& mid,
330 int64_t timestamp_us) {
331 auto inbound_audio = std::make_unique<RTCInboundRTPStreamStats>(
332 /*id=*/RTCInboundRTPStreamStatsIDFromSSRC(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO,
333 voice_receiver_info.ssrc()),
334 timestamp_us);
335 SetInboundRTPStreamStatsFromMediaReceiverInfo(voice_receiver_info,
336 inbound_audio.get());
337 inbound_audio->media_type = "audio";
338 inbound_audio->kind = "audio";
339 if (voice_receiver_info.codec_payload_type) {
340 inbound_audio->codec_id = RTCCodecStatsIDFromMidDirectionAndPayload(
341 mid, /*inbound=*/true, *voice_receiver_info.codec_payload_type);
342 }
343 inbound_audio->jitter = static_cast<double>(voice_receiver_info.jitter_ms) /
344 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
345 inbound_audio->jitter_buffer_delay =
346 voice_receiver_info.jitter_buffer_delay_seconds;
347 inbound_audio->jitter_buffer_emitted_count =
348 voice_receiver_info.jitter_buffer_emitted_count;
349 inbound_audio->total_samples_received =
350 voice_receiver_info.total_samples_received;
351 inbound_audio->concealed_samples = voice_receiver_info.concealed_samples;
352 inbound_audio->silent_concealed_samples =
353 voice_receiver_info.silent_concealed_samples;
354 inbound_audio->concealment_events = voice_receiver_info.concealment_events;
355 inbound_audio->inserted_samples_for_deceleration =
356 voice_receiver_info.inserted_samples_for_deceleration;
357 inbound_audio->removed_samples_for_acceleration =
358 voice_receiver_info.removed_samples_for_acceleration;
359 if (voice_receiver_info.audio_level >= 0) {
360 inbound_audio->audio_level =
361 DoubleAudioLevelFromIntAudioLevel(voice_receiver_info.audio_level);
362 }
363 inbound_audio->total_audio_energy = voice_receiver_info.total_output_energy;
364 inbound_audio->total_samples_duration =
365 voice_receiver_info.total_output_duration;
366 // |fir_count|, |pli_count| and |sli_count| are only valid for video and are
367 // purposefully left undefined for audio.
368 if (voice_receiver_info.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms) {
369 inbound_audio->last_packet_received_timestamp = static_cast<double>(
370 *voice_receiver_info.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms);
371 }
372 if (voice_receiver_info.estimated_playout_ntp_timestamp_ms) {
373 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10529): Fix time origin.
374 inbound_audio->estimated_playout_timestamp = static_cast<double>(
375 *voice_receiver_info.estimated_playout_ntp_timestamp_ms);
376 }
377 inbound_audio->fec_packets_received =
378 voice_receiver_info.fec_packets_received;
379 inbound_audio->fec_packets_discarded =
380 voice_receiver_info.fec_packets_discarded;
381 return inbound_audio;
382}

384std::unique_ptr<RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats>
385CreateRemoteOutboundAudioStreamStats(
386 const cricket::VoiceReceiverInfo& voice_receiver_info,
387 const std::string& mid,
388 const std::string& inbound_audio_id,
389 const std::string& transport_id) {
390 if (!voice_receiver_info.last_sender_report_timestamp_ms.has_value()) {
391 // Cannot create `RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats` when the RTCP SR arrival
392 // timestamp is not available - i.e., until the first sender report is
393 // received.
394 return nullptr;
395 }
396 RTC_DCHECK_GT(voice_receiver_info.sender_reports_reports_count, 0);
397
398 // Create.
399 auto stats = std::make_unique<RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats>(
400 /*id=*/RTCRemoteOutboundRTPStreamStatsIDFromSSRC(
401 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, voice_receiver_info.ssrc()),
402 /*timestamp_us=*/rtc::kNumMicrosecsPerMillisec *
403 voice_receiver_info.last_sender_report_timestamp_ms.value());
404
405 // Populate.
406 // - RTCRtpStreamStats.
407 stats->ssrc = voice_receiver_info.ssrc();
408 stats->kind = "audio";
409 stats->transport_id = transport_id;
410 stats->codec_id = RTCCodecStatsIDFromMidDirectionAndPayload(
411 mid,
412 /*inbound=*/true, // Remote-outbound same as local-inbound.
413 *voice_receiver_info.codec_payload_type);
414 // - RTCSentRtpStreamStats.
415 stats->packets_sent = voice_receiver_info.sender_reports_packets_sent;
416 stats->bytes_sent = voice_receiver_info.sender_reports_bytes_sent;
417 // - RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats.
418 stats->local_id = inbound_audio_id;
419 RTC_DCHECK(
420 voice_receiver_info.last_sender_report_remote_timestamp_ms.has_value());
421 stats->remote_timestamp = static_cast<double>(
422 voice_receiver_info.last_sender_report_remote_timestamp_ms.value());
423 stats->reports_sent = voice_receiver_info.sender_reports_reports_count;
424
425 return stats;
426}

428void SetInboundRTPStreamStatsFromVideoReceiverInfo(
429 const std::string& mid,
430 const cricket::VideoReceiverInfo& video_receiver_info,
431 RTCInboundRTPStreamStats* inbound_video) {
432 SetInboundRTPStreamStatsFromMediaReceiverInfo(video_receiver_info,
433 inbound_video);
434 inbound_video->media_type = "video";
435 inbound_video->kind = "video";
436 if (video_receiver_info.codec_payload_type) {
437 inbound_video->codec_id = RTCCodecStatsIDFromMidDirectionAndPayload(
438 mid, /*inbound=*/true, *video_receiver_info.codec_payload_type);
439 }
440 inbound_video->jitter = static_cast<double>(video_receiver_info.jitter_ms) /
441 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
442 inbound_video->fir_count =
443 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_receiver_info.firs_sent);
444 inbound_video->pli_count =
445 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_receiver_info.plis_sent);
446 inbound_video->nack_count =
447 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_receiver_info.nacks_sent);
448 inbound_video->frames_received = video_receiver_info.frames_received;
449 inbound_video->frames_decoded = video_receiver_info.frames_decoded;
450 inbound_video->frames_dropped = video_receiver_info.frames_dropped;
451 inbound_video->key_frames_decoded = video_receiver_info.key_frames_decoded;
452 if (video_receiver_info.frame_width > 0) {
453 inbound_video->frame_width =
454 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_receiver_info.frame_width);
455 }
456 if (video_receiver_info.frame_height > 0) {
457 inbound_video->frame_height =
458 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_receiver_info.frame_height);
459 }
460 if (video_receiver_info.framerate_rcvd > 0) {
461 inbound_video->frames_per_second = video_receiver_info.framerate_rcvd;
462 }
463 if (video_receiver_info.qp_sum)
464 inbound_video->qp_sum = *video_receiver_info.qp_sum;
465 inbound_video->total_decode_time =
466 static_cast<double>(video_receiver_info.total_decode_time_ms) /
467 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
468 inbound_video->total_inter_frame_delay =
469 video_receiver_info.total_inter_frame_delay;
470 inbound_video->total_squared_inter_frame_delay =
471 video_receiver_info.total_squared_inter_frame_delay;
472 if (video_receiver_info.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms) {
473 inbound_video->last_packet_received_timestamp = static_cast<double>(
474 *video_receiver_info.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms);
475 }
476 if (video_receiver_info.estimated_playout_ntp_timestamp_ms) {
477 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10529): Fix time origin if needed.
478 inbound_video->estimated_playout_timestamp = static_cast<double>(
479 *video_receiver_info.estimated_playout_ntp_timestamp_ms);
480 }
481 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10529): When info's |content_info| is optional
482 // support the "unspecified" value.
483 if (video_receiver_info.content_type == VideoContentType::SCREENSHARE)
484 inbound_video->content_type = RTCContentType::kScreenshare;
485 if (!video_receiver_info.decoder_implementation_name.empty()) {
486 inbound_video->decoder_implementation =
487 video_receiver_info.decoder_implementation_name;
488 }
489}

525void SetOutboundRTPStreamStatsFromVideoSenderInfo(
526 const std::string& mid,
527 const cricket::VideoSenderInfo& video_sender_info,
528 RTCOutboundRTPStreamStats* outbound_video) {
529 SetOutboundRTPStreamStatsFromMediaSenderInfo(video_sender_info,
530 outbound_video);
531 outbound_video->media_type = "video";
532 outbound_video->kind = "video";
533 if (video_sender_info.codec_payload_type) {
534 outbound_video->codec_id = RTCCodecStatsIDFromMidDirectionAndPayload(
535 mid, /*inbound=*/false, *video_sender_info.codec_payload_type);
536 }
537 outbound_video->fir_count =
538 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_sender_info.firs_rcvd);
539 outbound_video->pli_count =
540 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_sender_info.plis_rcvd);
541 outbound_video->nack_count =
542 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_sender_info.nacks_rcvd);
543 if (video_sender_info.qp_sum)
544 outbound_video->qp_sum = *video_sender_info.qp_sum;
545 outbound_video->frames_encoded = video_sender_info.frames_encoded;
546 outbound_video->key_frames_encoded = video_sender_info.key_frames_encoded;
547 outbound_video->total_encode_time =
548 static_cast<double>(video_sender_info.total_encode_time_ms) /
549 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
550 outbound_video->total_encoded_bytes_target =
551 video_sender_info.total_encoded_bytes_target;
552 if (video_sender_info.send_frame_width > 0) {
553 outbound_video->frame_width =
554 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_sender_info.send_frame_width);
555 }
556 if (video_sender_info.send_frame_height > 0) {
557 outbound_video->frame_height =
558 static_cast<uint32_t>(video_sender_info.send_frame_height);
559 }
560 if (video_sender_info.framerate_sent > 0) {
561 outbound_video->frames_per_second = video_sender_info.framerate_sent;
562 }
563 outbound_video->frames_sent = video_sender_info.frames_sent;
564 outbound_video->huge_frames_sent = video_sender_info.huge_frames_sent;
565 outbound_video->total_packet_send_delay =
566 static_cast<double>(video_sender_info.total_packet_send_delay_ms) /
567 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
568 outbound_video->quality_limitation_reason =
569 QualityLimitationReasonToRTCQualityLimitationReason(
570 video_sender_info.quality_limitation_reason);
571 outbound_video->quality_limitation_resolution_changes =
572 video_sender_info.quality_limitation_resolution_changes;
573 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/10529): When info's |content_info| is
574 // optional, support the "unspecified" value.
575 if (video_sender_info.content_type == VideoContentType::SCREENSHARE)
576 outbound_video->content_type = RTCContentType::kScreenshare;
577 if (!video_sender_info.encoder_implementation_name.empty()) {
578 outbound_video->encoder_implementation =
579 video_sender_info.encoder_implementation_name;
580 }
581 if (video_sender_info.rid) {
582 outbound_video->rid = *video_sender_info.rid;
583 }
584}
585
586std::unique_ptr<RTCRemoteInboundRtpStreamStats>
587ProduceRemoteInboundRtpStreamStatsFromReportBlockData(
588 const ReportBlockData& report_block_data,
589 cricket::MediaType media_type,
590 const std::map<std::string, RTCOutboundRTPStreamStats*>& outbound_rtps,
591 const RTCStatsReport& report) {
592 const auto& report_block = report_block_data.report_block();
593 // RTCStats' timestamp generally refers to when the metric was sampled, but
594 // for "remote-[outbound/inbound]-rtp" it refers to the local time when the
595 // Report Block was received.
596 auto remote_inbound = std::make_unique<RTCRemoteInboundRtpStreamStats>(
597 RTCRemoteInboundRtpStreamStatsIdFromSourceSsrc(media_type,
598 report_block.source_ssrc),
599 /*timestamp=*/report_block_data.report_block_timestamp_utc_us());
600 remote_inbound->ssrc = report_block.source_ssrc;
601 remote_inbound->kind =
602 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ? "audio" : "video";
603 remote_inbound->packets_lost = report_block.packets_lost;
604 remote_inbound->fraction_lost =
605 static_cast<double>(report_block.fraction_lost) / (1 << 8);
606 remote_inbound->round_trip_time =
607 static_cast<double>(report_block_data.last_rtt_ms()) /
608 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
609 remote_inbound->total_round_trip_time =
610 static_cast<double>(report_block_data.sum_rtt_ms()) /
611 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
612 remote_inbound->round_trip_time_measurements =
613 report_block_data.num_rtts();
614
615 std::string local_id =
616 RTCOutboundRTPStreamStatsIDFromSSRC(media_type, report_block.source_ssrc);
617 // Look up local stat from |outbound_rtps| where the pointers are non-const.
618 auto local_id_it = outbound_rtps.find(local_id);
619 if (local_id_it != outbound_rtps.end()) {
620 remote_inbound->local_id = local_id;
621 auto& outbound_rtp = *local_id_it->second;
622 outbound_rtp.remote_id = remote_inbound->id();
623 // The RTP/RTCP transport is obtained from the
624 // RTCOutboundRtpStreamStats's transport.
625 const auto* transport_from_id = outbound_rtp.transport_id.is_defined()
626 ? report.Get(*outbound_rtp.transport_id)
627 : nullptr;
628 if (transport_from_id) {
629 const auto& transport = transport_from_id->cast_to<RTCTransportStats>();
630 // If RTP and RTCP are not multiplexed, there is a separate RTCP
631 // transport paired with the RTP transport, otherwise the same
632 // transport is used for RTCP and RTP.
633 remote_inbound->transport_id =
634 transport.rtcp_transport_stats_id.is_defined()
635 ? *transport.rtcp_transport_stats_id
636 : *outbound_rtp.transport_id;
637 }
638 // We're assuming the same codec is used on both ends. However if the
639 // codec is switched out on the fly we may have received a Report Block
640 // based on the previous codec and there is no way to tell which point in
641 // time the codec changed for the remote end.
642 const auto* codec_from_id = outbound_rtp.codec_id.is_defined()
643 ? report.Get(*outbound_rtp.codec_id)
644 : nullptr;
645 if (codec_from_id) {
646 remote_inbound->codec_id = *outbound_rtp.codec_id;
647 const auto& codec = codec_from_id->cast_to<RTCCodecStats>();
648 if (codec.clock_rate.is_defined()) {
649 // The Report Block jitter is expressed in RTP timestamp units
650 // (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3550#section-6.4.1). To convert this
651 // to seconds we divide by the codec's clock rate.
652 remote_inbound->jitter =
653 static_cast<double>(report_block.jitter) / *codec.clock_rate;
654 }
655 }
656 }
657 return remote_inbound;
658}
659
660void ProduceCertificateStatsFromSSLCertificateStats(
661 int64_t timestamp_us,
662 const rtc::SSLCertificateStats& certificate_stats,
663 RTCStatsReport* report) {
664 RTCCertificateStats* prev_certificate_stats = nullptr;
665 for (const rtc::SSLCertificateStats* s = &certificate_stats; s;
666 s = s->issuer.get()) {
667 std::string certificate_stats_id =
668 RTCCertificateIDFromFingerprint(s->fingerprint);
669 // It is possible for the same certificate to show up multiple times, e.g.
670 // if local and remote side use the same certificate in a loopback call.
671 // If the report already contains stats for this certificate, skip it.
672 if (report->Get(certificate_stats_id)) {
673 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(s, &certificate_stats);
674 break;
675 }
676 RTCCertificateStats* certificate_stats =
677 new RTCCertificateStats(certificate_stats_id, timestamp_us);
678 certificate_stats->fingerprint = s->fingerprint;
679 certificate_stats->fingerprint_algorithm = s->fingerprint_algorithm;
680 certificate_stats->base64_certificate = s->base64_certificate;
681 if (prev_certificate_stats)
682 prev_certificate_stats->issuer_certificate_id = certificate_stats->id();
683 report->AddStats(std::unique_ptr<RTCCertificateStats>(certificate_stats));
684 prev_certificate_stats = certificate_stats;
685 }
686}
687
688const std::string& ProduceIceCandidateStats(int64_t timestamp_us,
689 const cricket::Candidate& candidate,
690 bool is_local,
691 const std::string& transport_id,
692 RTCStatsReport* report) {
693 const std::string& id = "RTCIceCandidate_" + candidate.id();
694 const RTCStats* stats = report->Get(id);
695 if (!stats) {
696 std::unique_ptr<RTCIceCandidateStats> candidate_stats;
697 if (is_local)
698 candidate_stats.reset(new RTCLocalIceCandidateStats(id, timestamp_us));
699 else
700 candidate_stats.reset(new RTCRemoteIceCandidateStats(id, timestamp_us));
701 candidate_stats->transport_id = transport_id;
702 if (is_local) {
703 candidate_stats->network_type =
704 NetworkAdapterTypeToStatsType(candidate.network_type());
705 if (candidate.type() == cricket::RELAY_PORT_TYPE) {
706 std::string relay_protocol = candidate.relay_protocol();
707 RTC_DCHECK(relay_protocol.compare("udp") == 0 ||
708 relay_protocol.compare("tcp") == 0 ||
709 relay_protocol.compare("tls") == 0);
710 candidate_stats->relay_protocol = relay_protocol;
711 }
712 } else {
713 // We don't expect to know the adapter type of remote candidates.
714 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_UNKNOWN, candidate.network_type());
715 }
716 candidate_stats->ip = candidate.address().ipaddr().ToString();
717 candidate_stats->address = candidate.address().ipaddr().ToString();
718 candidate_stats->port = static_cast<int32_t>(candidate.address().port());
719 candidate_stats->protocol = candidate.protocol();
720 candidate_stats->candidate_type =
721 CandidateTypeToRTCIceCandidateType(candidate.type());
722 candidate_stats->priority = static_cast<int32_t>(candidate.priority());
723
724 stats = candidate_stats.get();
725 report->AddStats(std::move(candidate_stats));
726 }
727 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(stats->type(), is_local ? RTCLocalIceCandidateStats::kType
728 : RTCRemoteIceCandidateStats::kType);
729 return stats->id();
730}

898
899void ProduceSenderMediaTrackStats(
900 int64_t timestamp_us,
901 const TrackMediaInfoMap& track_media_info_map,
902 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal>> senders,
903 RTCStatsReport* report) {
904 // This function iterates over the senders to generate outgoing track stats.
905
906 // TODO(hbos): Return stats of detached tracks. We have to perform stats
907 // gathering at the time of detachment to get accurate stats and timestamps.
908 // https://crbug.com/659137
909 for (const auto& sender : senders) {
910 if (sender->media_type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
911 AudioTrackInterface* track =
912 static_cast<AudioTrackInterface*>(sender->track().get());
913 if (!track)
914 continue;
915 cricket::VoiceSenderInfo null_sender_info;
916 const cricket::VoiceSenderInfo* voice_sender_info = &null_sender_info;
917 // TODO(hta): Checking on ssrc is not proper. There should be a way
918 // to see from a sender whether it's connected or not.
919 // Related to https://crbug.com/8694 (using ssrc 0 to indicate "none")
920 if (sender->ssrc() != 0) {
921 // When pc.close is called, sender info is discarded, so
922 // we generate zeroes instead. Bug: It should be retained.
923 // https://crbug.com/807174
924 const cricket::VoiceSenderInfo* sender_info =
925 track_media_info_map.GetVoiceSenderInfoBySsrc(sender->ssrc());
926 if (sender_info) {
927 voice_sender_info = sender_info;
928 } else {
929 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
930 << "RTCStatsCollector: No voice sender info for sender with ssrc "
931 << sender->ssrc();
932 }
933 }
934 std::unique_ptr<RTCMediaStreamTrackStats> audio_track_stats =
935 ProduceMediaStreamTrackStatsFromVoiceSenderInfo(
936 timestamp_us, *track, *voice_sender_info, sender->AttachmentId());
937 report->AddStats(std::move(audio_track_stats));
938 } else if (sender->media_type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
939 VideoTrackInterface* track =
940 static_cast<VideoTrackInterface*>(sender->track().get());
941 if (!track)
942 continue;
943 cricket::VideoSenderInfo null_sender_info;
944 const cricket::VideoSenderInfo* video_sender_info = &null_sender_info;
945 // TODO(hta): Check on state not ssrc when state is available
946 // Related to https://bugs.webrtc.org/8694 (using ssrc 0 to indicate
947 // "none")
948 if (sender->ssrc() != 0) {
949 // When pc.close is called, sender info is discarded, so
950 // we generate zeroes instead. Bug: It should be retained.
951 // https://crbug.com/807174
952 const cricket::VideoSenderInfo* sender_info =
953 track_media_info_map.GetVideoSenderInfoBySsrc(sender->ssrc());
954 if (sender_info) {
955 video_sender_info = sender_info;
956 } else {
957 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "No video sender info for sender with ssrc "
958 << sender->ssrc();
959 }
960 }
961 std::unique_ptr<RTCMediaStreamTrackStats> video_track_stats =
962 ProduceMediaStreamTrackStatsFromVideoSenderInfo(
963 timestamp_us, *track, *video_sender_info, sender->AttachmentId());
964 report->AddStats(std::move(video_track_stats));
965 } else {
966 RTC_NOTREACHED();
967 }
968 }
969}
970
971void ProduceReceiverMediaTrackStats(
972 int64_t timestamp_us,
973 const TrackMediaInfoMap& track_media_info_map,
974 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInternal>> receivers,
975 RTCStatsReport* report) {
976 // This function iterates over the receivers to find the remote tracks.
977 for (const auto& receiver : receivers) {
978 if (receiver->media_type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
979 AudioTrackInterface* track =
980 static_cast<AudioTrackInterface*>(receiver->track().get());
981 const cricket::VoiceReceiverInfo* voice_receiver_info =
982 track_media_info_map.GetVoiceReceiverInfo(*track);
983 if (!voice_receiver_info) {
984 continue;
985 }
986 std::unique_ptr<RTCMediaStreamTrackStats> audio_track_stats =
987 ProduceMediaStreamTrackStatsFromVoiceReceiverInfo(
988 timestamp_us, *track, *voice_receiver_info,
989 receiver->AttachmentId());
990 report->AddStats(std::move(audio_track_stats));
991 } else if (receiver->media_type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
992 VideoTrackInterface* track =
993 static_cast<VideoTrackInterface*>(receiver->track().get());
994 const cricket::VideoReceiverInfo* video_receiver_info =
995 track_media_info_map.GetVideoReceiverInfo(*track);
996 if (!video_receiver_info) {
997 continue;
998 }
999 std::unique_ptr<RTCMediaStreamTrackStats> video_track_stats =
1000 ProduceMediaStreamTrackStatsFromVideoReceiverInfo(
1001 timestamp_us, *track, *video_receiver_info,
1002 receiver->AttachmentId());
1003 report->AddStats(std::move(video_track_stats));
1004 } else {
1005 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1006 }
1007 }
1008}
1009
1010rtc::scoped_refptr<RTCStatsReport> CreateReportFilteredBySelector(
1011 bool filter_by_sender_selector,
1012 rtc::scoped_refptr<const RTCStatsReport> report,
1013 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal> sender_selector,
1014 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInternal> receiver_selector) {
1015 std::vector<std::string> rtpstream_ids;
1016 if (filter_by_sender_selector) {
1017 // Filter mode: RTCStatsCollector::RequestInfo::kSenderSelector
1018 if (sender_selector) {
1019 // Find outbound-rtp(s) of the sender, i.e. the outbound-rtp(s) that
1020 // reference the sender stats.
1021 // Because we do not implement sender stats, we look at outbound-rtp(s)
1022 // that reference the track attachment stats for the sender instead.
1023 std::string track_id =
1024 RTCMediaStreamTrackStatsIDFromDirectionAndAttachment(
1025 kSender, sender_selector->AttachmentId());
1026 for (const auto& stats : *report) {
1027 if (stats.type() != RTCOutboundRTPStreamStats::kType)
1028 continue;
1029 const auto& outbound_rtp = stats.cast_to<RTCOutboundRTPStreamStats>();
1030 if (outbound_rtp.track_id.is_defined() &&
1031 *outbound_rtp.track_id == track_id) {
1032 rtpstream_ids.push_back(outbound_rtp.id());
1033 }
1034 }
1035 }
1036 } else {
1037 // Filter mode: RTCStatsCollector::RequestInfo::kReceiverSelector
1038 if (receiver_selector) {
1039 // Find inbound-rtp(s) of the receiver, i.e. the inbound-rtp(s) that
1040 // reference the receiver stats.
1041 // Because we do not implement receiver stats, we look at inbound-rtp(s)
1042 // that reference the track attachment stats for the receiver instead.
1043 std::string track_id =
1044 RTCMediaStreamTrackStatsIDFromDirectionAndAttachment(
1045 kReceiver, receiver_selector->AttachmentId());
1046 for (const auto& stats : *report) {
1047 if (stats.type() != RTCInboundRTPStreamStats::kType)
1048 continue;
1049 const auto& inbound_rtp = stats.cast_to<RTCInboundRTPStreamStats>();
1050 if (inbound_rtp.track_id.is_defined() &&
1051 *inbound_rtp.track_id == track_id) {
1052 rtpstream_ids.push_back(inbound_rtp.id());
1053 }
1054 }
1055 }
1056 }
1057 if (rtpstream_ids.empty())
1058 return RTCStatsReport::Create(report->timestamp_us());
1059 return TakeReferencedStats(report->Copy(), rtpstream_ids);
1060}

1144
1145void RTCStatsCollector::GetStatsReportInternal(
1146 RTCStatsCollector::RequestInfo request) {
1147 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1148 requests_.push_back(std::move(request));
1149
1150 // "Now" using a monotonically increasing timer.
1151 int64_t cache_now_us = rtc::TimeMicros();
1152 if (cached_report_ &&
1153 cache_now_us - cache_timestamp_us_ <= cache_lifetime_us_) {
1154 // We have a fresh cached report to deliver. Deliver asynchronously, since
1155 // the caller may not be expecting a synchronous callback, and it avoids
1156 // reentrancy problems.
1157 std::vector<RequestInfo> requests;
1158 requests.swap(requests_);
1159
1160 // Task subclass to take ownership of the requests.
1161 // TODO(nisse): Delete when we can use C++14, and do lambda capture with
1162 // std::move.
1163 class DeliveryTask : public QueuedTask {
1164 public:
1165 DeliveryTask(rtc::scoped_refptr<RTCStatsCollector> collector,
1166 rtc::scoped_refptr<const RTCStatsReport> cached_report,
1167 std::vector<RequestInfo> requests)
1168 : collector_(collector),
1169 cached_report_(cached_report),
1170 requests_(std::move(requests)) {}
1171 bool Run() override {
1172 collector_->DeliverCachedReport(cached_report_, std::move(requests_));
1173 return true;
1174 }
1175
1176 private:
1177 rtc::scoped_refptr<RTCStatsCollector> collector_;
1178 rtc::scoped_refptr<const RTCStatsReport> cached_report_;
1179 std::vector<RequestInfo> requests_;
1180 };
1181 signaling_thread_->PostTask(std::make_unique<DeliveryTask>(
1182 this, cached_report_, std::move(requests)));
1183 } else if (!num_pending_partial_reports_) {
1184 // Only start gathering stats if we're not already gathering stats. In the
1185 // case of already gathering stats, |callback_| will be invoked when there
1186 // are no more pending partial reports.
1187
1188 // "Now" using a system clock, relative to the UNIX epoch (Jan 1, 1970,
1189 // UTC), in microseconds. The system clock could be modified and is not
1190 // necessarily monotonically increasing.
1191 int64_t timestamp_us = rtc::TimeUTCMicros();
1192
1193 num_pending_partial_reports_ = 2;
1194 partial_report_timestamp_us_ = cache_now_us;
1195
1196 // Prepare |transceiver_stats_infos_| and |call_stats_| for use in
1197 // |ProducePartialResultsOnNetworkThread| and
1198 // |ProducePartialResultsOnSignalingThread|.
1199 PrepareTransceiverStatsInfosAndCallStats_s_w_n();
1200 // Don't touch |network_report_| on the signaling thread until
1201 // ProducePartialResultsOnNetworkThread() has signaled the
1202 // |network_report_event_|.
1203 network_report_event_.Reset();
1204 rtc::scoped_refptr<RTCStatsCollector> collector(this);
1205 network_thread_->PostTask(
1206 RTC_FROM_HERE,
1207 [collector, sctp_transport_name = pc_->sctp_transport_name(),
1208 timestamp_us]() mutable {
1209 collector->ProducePartialResultsOnNetworkThread(
1210 timestamp_us, std::move(sctp_transport_name));
1211 });
1212 ProducePartialResultsOnSignalingThread(timestamp_us);
1213 }
1214}
1215
1216void RTCStatsCollector::ClearCachedStatsReport() {
1217 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1218 cached_report_ = nullptr;
1219}
1220
1221void RTCStatsCollector::WaitForPendingRequest() {
1222 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1223 // If a request is pending, blocks until the |network_report_event_| is
1224 // signaled and then delivers the result. Otherwise this is a NO-OP.
1225 MergeNetworkReport_s();
1226}
1227
1228void RTCStatsCollector::ProducePartialResultsOnSignalingThread(
1229 int64_t timestamp_us) {
1230 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1231 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1232
1233 partial_report_ = RTCStatsReport::Create(timestamp_us);
1234
1235 ProducePartialResultsOnSignalingThreadImpl(timestamp_us,
1236 partial_report_.get());
1237
1238 // ProducePartialResultsOnSignalingThread() is running synchronously on the
1239 // signaling thread, so it is always the first partial result delivered on the
1240 // signaling thread. The request is not complete until MergeNetworkReport_s()
1241 // happens; we don't have to do anything here.
1242 RTC_DCHECK_GT(num_pending_partial_reports_, 1);
1243 --num_pending_partial_reports_;
1244}
1245
1246void RTCStatsCollector::ProducePartialResultsOnSignalingThreadImpl(
1247 int64_t timestamp_us,
1248 RTCStatsReport* partial_report) {
1249 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1250 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1251
1252 ProduceDataChannelStats_s(timestamp_us, partial_report);
1253 ProduceMediaStreamStats_s(timestamp_us, partial_report);
1254 ProduceMediaStreamTrackStats_s(timestamp_us, partial_report);
1255 ProduceMediaSourceStats_s(timestamp_us, partial_report);
1256 ProducePeerConnectionStats_s(timestamp_us, partial_report);
1257}
1258
1259void RTCStatsCollector::ProducePartialResultsOnNetworkThread(
1260 int64_t timestamp_us,
1261 absl::optional<std::string> sctp_transport_name) {
1262 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1263 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1264
1265 // Touching |network_report_| on this thread is safe by this method because
1266 // |network_report_event_| is reset before this method is invoked.
1267 network_report_ = RTCStatsReport::Create(timestamp_us);
1268
1269 std::set<std::string> transport_names;
1270 if (sctp_transport_name) {
1271 transport_names.emplace(std::move(*sctp_transport_name));
1272 }
1273
1274 for (const auto& info : transceiver_stats_infos_) {
1275 if (info.transport_name)
1276 transport_names.insert(*info.transport_name);
1277 }
1278
1279 std::map<std::string, cricket::TransportStats> transport_stats_by_name =
1280 pc_->GetTransportStatsByNames(transport_names);
1281 std::map<std::string, CertificateStatsPair> transport_cert_stats =
1282 PrepareTransportCertificateStats_n(transport_stats_by_name);
1283
1284 ProducePartialResultsOnNetworkThreadImpl(
1285 timestamp_us, transport_stats_by_name, transport_cert_stats,
1286 network_report_.get());
1287
1288 // Signal that it is now safe to touch |network_report_| on the signaling
1289 // thread, and post a task to merge it into the final results.
1290 network_report_event_.Set();
1291 rtc::scoped_refptr<RTCStatsCollector> collector(this);
1292 signaling_thread_->PostTask(
1293 RTC_FROM_HERE, [collector] { collector->MergeNetworkReport_s(); });
1294}
1295
1296void RTCStatsCollector::ProducePartialResultsOnNetworkThreadImpl(
1297 int64_t timestamp_us,
1298 const std::map<std::string, cricket::TransportStats>&
1299 transport_stats_by_name,
1300 const std::map<std::string, CertificateStatsPair>& transport_cert_stats,
1301 RTCStatsReport* partial_report) {
1302 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1303 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1304
1305 ProduceCertificateStats_n(timestamp_us, transport_cert_stats, partial_report);
1306 ProduceCodecStats_n(timestamp_us, transceiver_stats_infos_, partial_report);
1307 ProduceIceCandidateAndPairStats_n(timestamp_us, transport_stats_by_name,
1308 call_stats_, partial_report);
1309 ProduceTransportStats_n(timestamp_us, transport_stats_by_name,
1310 transport_cert_stats, partial_report);
1311 ProduceRTPStreamStats_n(timestamp_us, transceiver_stats_infos_,
1312 partial_report);
1313}
1314
1315void RTCStatsCollector::MergeNetworkReport_s() {
1316 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1317 // The |network_report_event_| must be signaled for it to be safe to touch
1318 // |network_report_|. This is normally not blocking, but if
1319 // WaitForPendingRequest() is called while a request is pending, we might have
1320 // to wait until the network thread is done touching |network_report_|.
1321 network_report_event_.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
1322 if (!network_report_) {
1323 // Normally, MergeNetworkReport_s() is executed because it is posted from
1324 // the network thread. But if WaitForPendingRequest() is called while a
1325 // request is pending, an early call to MergeNetworkReport_s() is made,
1326 // merging the report and setting |network_report_| to null. If so, when the
1327 // previously posted MergeNetworkReport_s() is later executed, the report is
1328 // already null and nothing needs to be done here.
1329 return;
1330 }
1331 RTC_DCHECK_GT(num_pending_partial_reports_, 0);
1332 RTC_DCHECK(partial_report_);
1333 partial_report_->TakeMembersFrom(network_report_);
1334 network_report_ = nullptr;
1335 --num_pending_partial_reports_;
1336 // |network_report_| is currently the only partial report collected
1337 // asynchronously, so |num_pending_partial_reports_| must now be 0 and we are
1338 // ready to deliver the result.
1339 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_pending_partial_reports_, 0);
1340 cache_timestamp_us_ = partial_report_timestamp_us_;
1341 cached_report_ = partial_report_;
1342 partial_report_ = nullptr;
1343 transceiver_stats_infos_.clear();
1344 // Trace WebRTC Stats when getStats is called on Javascript.
1345 // This allows access to WebRTC stats from trace logs. To enable them,
1346 // select the "webrtc_stats" category when recording traces.
1347 TRACE_EVENT_INSTANT1("webrtc_stats", "webrtc_stats", "report",
1348 cached_report_->ToJson());
1349
1350 // Deliver report and clear |requests_|.
1351 std::vector<RequestInfo> requests;
1352 requests.swap(requests_);
1353 DeliverCachedReport(cached_report_, std::move(requests));
1354}
1355
1356void RTCStatsCollector::DeliverCachedReport(
1357 rtc::scoped_refptr<const RTCStatsReport> cached_report,
1358 std::vector<RTCStatsCollector::RequestInfo> requests) {
1359 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1360 RTC_DCHECK(!requests.empty());
1361 RTC_DCHECK(cached_report);
1362
1363 for (const RequestInfo& request : requests) {
1364 if (request.filter_mode() == RequestInfo::FilterMode::kAll) {
1365 request.callback()->OnStatsDelivered(cached_report);
1366 } else {
1367 bool filter_by_sender_selector;
1368 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal> sender_selector;
1369 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInternal> receiver_selector;
1370 if (request.filter_mode() == RequestInfo::FilterMode::kSenderSelector) {
1371 filter_by_sender_selector = true;
1372 sender_selector = request.sender_selector();
1373 } else {
1374 RTC_DCHECK(request.filter_mode() ==
1375 RequestInfo::FilterMode::kReceiverSelector);
1376 filter_by_sender_selector = false;
1377 receiver_selector = request.receiver_selector();
1378 }
1379 request.callback()->OnStatsDelivered(CreateReportFilteredBySelector(
1380 filter_by_sender_selector, cached_report, sender_selector,
1381 receiver_selector));
1382 }
1383 }
1384}

1405void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceCodecStats_n(
1406 int64_t timestamp_us,
1407 const std::vector<RtpTransceiverStatsInfo>& transceiver_stats_infos,
1408 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1409 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1410 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1411
1412 for (const auto& stats : transceiver_stats_infos) {
1413 if (!stats.mid) {
1414 continue;
1415 }
1416 std::string transport_id = RTCTransportStatsIDFromTransportChannel(
1417 *stats.transport_name, cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTP);
1418
1419 const cricket::VoiceMediaInfo* voice_media_info =
1420 stats.track_media_info_map->voice_media_info();
1421 const cricket::VideoMediaInfo* video_media_info =
1422 stats.track_media_info_map->video_media_info();
1423 // Audio
1424 if (voice_media_info) {
1425 // Inbound
1426 for (const auto& pair : voice_media_info->receive_codecs) {
1427 report->AddStats(CodecStatsFromRtpCodecParameters(
1428 timestamp_us, *stats.mid, transport_id, true, pair.second));
1429 }
1430 // Outbound
1431 for (const auto& pair : voice_media_info->send_codecs) {
1432 report->AddStats(CodecStatsFromRtpCodecParameters(
1433 timestamp_us, *stats.mid, transport_id, false, pair.second));
1434 }
1435 }
1436 // Video
1437 if (video_media_info) {
1438 // Inbound
1439 for (const auto& pair : video_media_info->receive_codecs) {
1440 report->AddStats(CodecStatsFromRtpCodecParameters(
1441 timestamp_us, *stats.mid, transport_id, true, pair.second));
1442 }
1443 // Outbound
1444 for (const auto& pair : video_media_info->send_codecs) {
1445 report->AddStats(CodecStatsFromRtpCodecParameters(
1446 timestamp_us, *stats.mid, transport_id, false, pair.second));
1447 }
1448 }
1449 }
1450}

1452void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceDataChannelStats_s(
1453 int64_t timestamp_us,
1454 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1455 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1456 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1457 std::vector<DataChannelStats> data_stats = pc_->GetDataChannelStats();
1458 for (const auto& stats : data_stats) {
1459 std::unique_ptr<RTCDataChannelStats> data_channel_stats(
1460 new RTCDataChannelStats(
1461 "RTCDataChannel_" + rtc::ToString(stats.internal_id),
1462 timestamp_us));
1463 data_channel_stats->label = std::move(stats.label);
1464 data_channel_stats->protocol = std::move(stats.protocol);
1465 data_channel_stats->data_channel_identifier = stats.id;
1466 data_channel_stats->state = DataStateToRTCDataChannelState(stats.state);
1467 data_channel_stats->messages_sent = stats.messages_sent;
1468 data_channel_stats->bytes_sent = stats.bytes_sent;
1469 data_channel_stats->messages_received = stats.messages_received;
1470 data_channel_stats->bytes_received = stats.bytes_received;
1471 report->AddStats(std::move(data_channel_stats));
1472 }
1473}
1474
1475void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceIceCandidateAndPairStats_n(
1476 int64_t timestamp_us,
1477 const std::map<std::string, cricket::TransportStats>&
1478 transport_stats_by_name,
1479 const Call::Stats& call_stats,
1480 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1481 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1482 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1483
1484 for (const auto& entry : transport_stats_by_name) {
1485 const std::string& transport_name = entry.first;
1486 const cricket::TransportStats& transport_stats = entry.second;
1487 for (const auto& channel_stats : transport_stats.channel_stats) {
1488 std::string transport_id = RTCTransportStatsIDFromTransportChannel(
1489 transport_name, channel_stats.component);
1490 for (const cricket::ConnectionInfo& info :
1491 channel_stats.ice_transport_stats.connection_infos) {
1492 std::unique_ptr<RTCIceCandidatePairStats> candidate_pair_stats(
1493 new RTCIceCandidatePairStats(
1494 RTCIceCandidatePairStatsIDFromConnectionInfo(info),
1495 timestamp_us));
1496
1497 candidate_pair_stats->transport_id = transport_id;
1498 // TODO(hbos): There could be other candidates that are not paired with
1499 // anything. We don't have a complete list. Local candidates come from
1500 // Port objects, and prflx candidates (both local and remote) are only
1501 // stored in candidate pairs. https://crbug.com/632723
1502 candidate_pair_stats->local_candidate_id = ProduceIceCandidateStats(
1503 timestamp_us, info.local_candidate, true, transport_id, report);
1504 candidate_pair_stats->remote_candidate_id = ProduceIceCandidateStats(
1505 timestamp_us, info.remote_candidate, false, transport_id, report);
1506 candidate_pair_stats->state =
1507 IceCandidatePairStateToRTCStatsIceCandidatePairState(info.state);
1508 candidate_pair_stats->priority = info.priority;
1509 candidate_pair_stats->nominated = info.nominated;
1510 // TODO(hbos): This writable is different than the spec. It goes to
1511 // false after a certain amount of time without a response passes.
1512 // https://crbug.com/633550
1513 candidate_pair_stats->writable = info.writable;
1514 candidate_pair_stats->bytes_sent =
1515 static_cast<uint64_t>(info.sent_total_bytes);
1516 candidate_pair_stats->bytes_received =
1517 static_cast<uint64_t>(info.recv_total_bytes);
1518 candidate_pair_stats->total_round_trip_time =
1519 static_cast<double>(info.total_round_trip_time_ms) /
1520 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
1521 if (info.current_round_trip_time_ms) {
1522 candidate_pair_stats->current_round_trip_time =
1523 static_cast<double>(*info.current_round_trip_time_ms) /
1524 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
1525 }
1526 if (info.best_connection) {
1527 // The bandwidth estimations we have are for the selected candidate
1528 // pair ("info.best_connection").
1529 RTC_DCHECK_GE(call_stats.send_bandwidth_bps, 0);
1530 RTC_DCHECK_GE(call_stats.recv_bandwidth_bps, 0);
1531 if (call_stats.send_bandwidth_bps > 0) {
1532 candidate_pair_stats->available_outgoing_bitrate =
1533 static_cast<double>(call_stats.send_bandwidth_bps);
1534 }
1535 if (call_stats.recv_bandwidth_bps > 0) {
1536 candidate_pair_stats->available_incoming_bitrate =
1537 static_cast<double>(call_stats.recv_bandwidth_bps);
1538 }
1539 }
1540 candidate_pair_stats->requests_received =
1541 static_cast<uint64_t>(info.recv_ping_requests);
1542 candidate_pair_stats->requests_sent = static_cast<uint64_t>(
1543 info.sent_ping_requests_before_first_response);
1544 candidate_pair_stats->responses_received =
1545 static_cast<uint64_t>(info.recv_ping_responses);
1546 candidate_pair_stats->responses_sent =
1547 static_cast<uint64_t>(info.sent_ping_responses);
1548 RTC_DCHECK_GE(info.sent_ping_requests_total,
1549 info.sent_ping_requests_before_first_response);
1550 candidate_pair_stats->consent_requests_sent = static_cast<uint64_t>(
1551 info.sent_ping_requests_total -
1552 info.sent_ping_requests_before_first_response);
1553
1554 report->AddStats(std::move(candidate_pair_stats));
1555 }
1556 }
1557 }
1558}

1560void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceMediaStreamStats_s(
1561 int64_t timestamp_us,
1562 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1563 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1564 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1565
1566 std::map<std::string, std::vector<std::string>> track_ids;
1567
1568 for (const auto& stats : transceiver_stats_infos_) {
1569 for (const auto& sender : stats.transceiver->senders()) {
1570 std::string track_id =
1571 RTCMediaStreamTrackStatsIDFromDirectionAndAttachment(
1572 kSender, sender->internal()->AttachmentId());
1573 for (auto& stream_id : sender->stream_ids()) {
1574 track_ids[stream_id].push_back(track_id);
1575 }
1576 }
1577 for (const auto& receiver : stats.transceiver->receivers()) {
1578 std::string track_id =
1579 RTCMediaStreamTrackStatsIDFromDirectionAndAttachment(
1580 kReceiver, receiver->internal()->AttachmentId());
1581 for (auto& stream : receiver->streams()) {
1582 track_ids[stream->id()].push_back(track_id);
1583 }
1584 }
1585 }
1586
1587 // Build stats for each stream ID known.
1588 for (auto& it : track_ids) {
1589 std::unique_ptr<RTCMediaStreamStats> stream_stats(
1590 new RTCMediaStreamStats("RTCMediaStream_" + it.first, timestamp_us));
1591 stream_stats->stream_identifier = it.first;
1592 stream_stats->track_ids = it.second;
1593 report->AddStats(std::move(stream_stats));
1594 }
1595}
1596
1597void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceMediaStreamTrackStats_s(
1598 int64_t timestamp_us,
1599 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1600 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1601 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1602
1603 for (const RtpTransceiverStatsInfo& stats : transceiver_stats_infos_) {
1604 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal>> senders;
1605 for (const auto& sender : stats.transceiver->senders()) {
1606 senders.push_back(sender->internal());
1607 }
1608 ProduceSenderMediaTrackStats(timestamp_us, *stats.track_media_info_map,
1609 senders, report);
1610
1611 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInternal>> receivers;
1612 for (const auto& receiver : stats.transceiver->receivers()) {
1613 receivers.push_back(receiver->internal());
1614 }
1615 ProduceReceiverMediaTrackStats(timestamp_us, *stats.track_media_info_map,
1616 receivers, report);
1617 }
1618}
1619
1620void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceMediaSourceStats_s(
1621 int64_t timestamp_us,
1622 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1623 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
1624 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1625
1626 for (const RtpTransceiverStatsInfo& transceiver_stats_info :
1627 transceiver_stats_infos_) {
1628 const auto& track_media_info_map =
1629 transceiver_stats_info.track_media_info_map;
1630 for (const auto& sender : transceiver_stats_info.transceiver->senders()) {
1631 const auto& sender_internal = sender->internal();
1632 const auto& track = sender_internal->track();
1633 if (!track)
1634 continue;
1635 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/10771): The same track could be attached
1636 // to multiple senders which should result in multiple senders referencing
1637 // the same media-source stats. When all media source related metrics are
1638 // moved to the track's source (e.g. input frame rate is moved from
1639 // cricket::VideoSenderInfo to VideoTrackSourceInterface::Stats and audio
1640 // levels are moved to the corresponding audio track/source object), don't
1641 // create separate media source stats objects on a per-attachment basis.
1642 std::unique_ptr<RTCMediaSourceStats> media_source_stats;
1643 if (track->kind() == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kAudioKind) {
1644 auto audio_source_stats = std::make_unique<RTCAudioSourceStats>(
1645 RTCMediaSourceStatsIDFromKindAndAttachment(
1646 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, sender_internal->AttachmentId()),
1647 timestamp_us);
1648 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/10771): We shouldn't need to have an
1649 // SSRC assigned (there shouldn't need to exist a send-stream, created
1650 // by an O/A exchange) in order to read audio media-source stats.
1651 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/8694): SSRC 0 shouldn't be a magic
1652 // value indicating no SSRC.
1653 if (sender_internal->ssrc() != 0) {
1654 auto* voice_sender_info =
1655 track_media_info_map->GetVoiceSenderInfoBySsrc(
1656 sender_internal->ssrc());
1657 if (voice_sender_info) {
1658 audio_source_stats->audio_level = DoubleAudioLevelFromIntAudioLevel(
1659 voice_sender_info->audio_level);
1660 audio_source_stats->total_audio_energy =
1661 voice_sender_info->total_input_energy;
1662 audio_source_stats->total_samples_duration =
1663 voice_sender_info->total_input_duration;
1664 }
1665 }
1666 media_source_stats = std::move(audio_source_stats);
1667 } else {
1668 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(MediaStreamTrackInterface::kVideoKind, track->kind());
1669 auto video_source_stats = std::make_unique<RTCVideoSourceStats>(
1670 RTCMediaSourceStatsIDFromKindAndAttachment(
1671 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, sender_internal->AttachmentId()),
1672 timestamp_us);
1673 auto* video_track = static_cast<VideoTrackInterface*>(track.get());
1674 auto* video_source = video_track->GetSource();
1675 VideoTrackSourceInterface::Stats source_stats;
1676 if (video_source && video_source->GetStats(&source_stats)) {
1677 video_source_stats->width = source_stats.input_width;
1678 video_source_stats->height = source_stats.input_height;
1679 }
1680 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/10771): We shouldn't need to have an
1681 // SSRC assigned (there shouldn't need to exist a send-stream, created
1682 // by an O/A exchange) in order to get framesPerSecond.
1683 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/8694): SSRC 0 shouldn't be a magic
1684 // value indicating no SSRC.
1685 if (sender_internal->ssrc() != 0) {
1686 auto* video_sender_info =
1687 track_media_info_map->GetVideoSenderInfoBySsrc(
1688 sender_internal->ssrc());
1689 if (video_sender_info) {
1690 video_source_stats->frames_per_second =
1691 video_sender_info->framerate_input;
1692 video_source_stats->frames = video_sender_info->frames;
1693 }
1694 }
1695 media_source_stats = std::move(video_source_stats);
1696 }
1697 media_source_stats->track_identifier = track->id();
1698 media_source_stats->kind = track->kind();
1699 report->AddStats(std::move(media_source_stats));
1700 }
1701 }
1702}

1735void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceAudioRTPStreamStats_n(
1736 int64_t timestamp_us,
1737 const RtpTransceiverStatsInfo& stats,
1738 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1739 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1740 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1741
1742 if (!stats.mid || !stats.transport_name) {
1743 return;
1744 }
1745 RTC_DCHECK(stats.track_media_info_map);
1746 const TrackMediaInfoMap& track_media_info_map = *stats.track_media_info_map;
1747 RTC_DCHECK(track_media_info_map.voice_media_info());
1748 std::string mid = *stats.mid;
1749 std::string transport_id = RTCTransportStatsIDFromTransportChannel(
1750 *stats.transport_name, cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTP);
1751 // Inbound and remote-outbound.
1752 // The remote-outbound stats are based on RTCP sender reports sent from the
1753 // remote endpoint providing metrics about the remote outbound streams.
1754 for (const cricket::VoiceReceiverInfo& voice_receiver_info :
1755 track_media_info_map.voice_media_info()->receivers) {
1756 if (!voice_receiver_info.connected())
1757 continue;
1758 // Inbound.
1759 auto inbound_audio =
1760 CreateInboundAudioStreamStats(voice_receiver_info, mid, timestamp_us);
1761 // TODO(hta): This lookup should look for the sender, not the track.
1762 rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioTrackInterface> audio_track =
1763 track_media_info_map.GetAudioTrack(voice_receiver_info);
1764 if (audio_track) {
1765 inbound_audio->track_id =
1766 RTCMediaStreamTrackStatsIDFromDirectionAndAttachment(
1767 kReceiver,
1768 track_media_info_map.GetAttachmentIdByTrack(audio_track).value());
1769 }
1770 inbound_audio->transport_id = transport_id;
1771 // Remote-outbound.
1772 auto remote_outbound_audio = CreateRemoteOutboundAudioStreamStats(
1773 voice_receiver_info, mid, inbound_audio->id(), transport_id);
1774 // Add stats.
1775 if (remote_outbound_audio) {
1776 // When the remote outbound stats are available, the remote ID for the
1777 // local inbound stats is set.
1778 inbound_audio->remote_id = remote_outbound_audio->id();
1779 report->AddStats(std::move(remote_outbound_audio));
1780 }
1781 report->AddStats(std::move(inbound_audio));
1782 }
1783 // Outbound.
1784 std::map<std::string, RTCOutboundRTPStreamStats*> audio_outbound_rtps;
1785 for (const cricket::VoiceSenderInfo& voice_sender_info :
1786 track_media_info_map.voice_media_info()->senders) {
1787 if (!voice_sender_info.connected())
1788 continue;
1789 auto outbound_audio = std::make_unique<RTCOutboundRTPStreamStats>(
1790 RTCOutboundRTPStreamStatsIDFromSSRC(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO,
1791 voice_sender_info.ssrc()),
1792 timestamp_us);
1793 SetOutboundRTPStreamStatsFromVoiceSenderInfo(mid, voice_sender_info,
1794 outbound_audio.get());
1795 rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioTrackInterface> audio_track =
1796 track_media_info_map.GetAudioTrack(voice_sender_info);
1797 if (audio_track) {
1798 int attachment_id =
1799 track_media_info_map.GetAttachmentIdByTrack(audio_track).value();
1800 outbound_audio->track_id =
1801 RTCMediaStreamTrackStatsIDFromDirectionAndAttachment(kSender,
1802 attachment_id);
1803 outbound_audio->media_source_id =
1804 RTCMediaSourceStatsIDFromKindAndAttachment(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO,
1805 attachment_id);
1806 }
1807 outbound_audio->transport_id = transport_id;
1808 audio_outbound_rtps.insert(
1809 std::make_pair(outbound_audio->id(), outbound_audio.get()));
1810 report->AddStats(std::move(outbound_audio));
1811 }
1812 // Remote-inbound.
1813 // These are Report Block-based, information sent from the remote endpoint,
1814 // providing metrics about our Outbound streams. We take advantage of the fact
1815 // that RTCOutboundRtpStreamStats, RTCCodecStats and RTCTransport have already
1816 // been added to the report.
1817 for (const cricket::VoiceSenderInfo& voice_sender_info :
1818 track_media_info_map.voice_media_info()->senders) {
1819 for (const auto& report_block_data : voice_sender_info.report_block_datas) {
1820 report->AddStats(ProduceRemoteInboundRtpStreamStatsFromReportBlockData(
1821 report_block_data, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, audio_outbound_rtps,
1822 *report));
1823 }
1824 }
1825}

1910void RTCStatsCollector::ProduceTransportStats_n(
1911 int64_t timestamp_us,
1912 const std::map<std::string, cricket::TransportStats>&
1913 transport_stats_by_name,
1914 const std::map<std::string, CertificateStatsPair>& transport_cert_stats,
1915 RTCStatsReport* report) const {
1916 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1917 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
1918
1919 for (const auto& entry : transport_stats_by_name) {
1920 const std::string& transport_name = entry.first;
1921 const cricket::TransportStats& transport_stats = entry.second;
1922
1923 // Get reference to RTCP channel, if it exists.
1924 std::string rtcp_transport_stats_id;
1925 for (const cricket::TransportChannelStats& channel_stats :
1926 transport_stats.channel_stats) {
1927 if (channel_stats.component == cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTCP) {
1928 rtcp_transport_stats_id = RTCTransportStatsIDFromTransportChannel(
1929 transport_name, channel_stats.component);
1930 break;
1931 }
1932 }
1933
1934 // Get reference to local and remote certificates of this transport, if they
1935 // exist.
1936 const auto& certificate_stats_it =
1937 transport_cert_stats.find(transport_name);
1938 RTC_DCHECK(certificate_stats_it != transport_cert_stats.cend());
1939 std::string local_certificate_id;
1940 if (certificate_stats_it->second.local) {
1941 local_certificate_id = RTCCertificateIDFromFingerprint(
1942 certificate_stats_it->second.local->fingerprint);
1943 }
1944 std::string remote_certificate_id;
1945 if (certificate_stats_it->second.remote) {
1946 remote_certificate_id = RTCCertificateIDFromFingerprint(
1947 certificate_stats_it->second.remote->fingerprint);
1948 }
1949
1950 // There is one transport stats for each channel.
1951 for (const cricket::TransportChannelStats& channel_stats :
1952 transport_stats.channel_stats) {
1953 std::unique_ptr<RTCTransportStats> transport_stats(
1954 new RTCTransportStats(RTCTransportStatsIDFromTransportChannel(
1955 transport_name, channel_stats.component),
1956 timestamp_us));
1957 transport_stats->bytes_sent = 0;
1958 transport_stats->packets_sent = 0;
1959 transport_stats->bytes_received = 0;
1960 transport_stats->packets_received = 0;
1961 transport_stats->dtls_state =
1962 DtlsTransportStateToRTCDtlsTransportState(channel_stats.dtls_state);
1963 transport_stats->selected_candidate_pair_changes =
1964 channel_stats.ice_transport_stats.selected_candidate_pair_changes;
1965 for (const cricket::ConnectionInfo& info :
1966 channel_stats.ice_transport_stats.connection_infos) {
1967 *transport_stats->bytes_sent += info.sent_total_bytes;
1968 *transport_stats->packets_sent +=
1969 info.sent_total_packets - info.sent_discarded_packets;
1970 *transport_stats->bytes_received += info.recv_total_bytes;
1971 *transport_stats->packets_received += info.packets_received;
1972 if (info.best_connection) {
1973 transport_stats->selected_candidate_pair_id =
1974 RTCIceCandidatePairStatsIDFromConnectionInfo(info);
1975 }
1976 }
1977 if (channel_stats.component != cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTCP &&
1978 !rtcp_transport_stats_id.empty()) {
1979 transport_stats->rtcp_transport_stats_id = rtcp_transport_stats_id;
1980 }
1981 if (!local_certificate_id.empty())
1982 transport_stats->local_certificate_id = local_certificate_id;
1983 if (!remote_certificate_id.empty())
1984 transport_stats->remote_certificate_id = remote_certificate_id;
1985 // Crypto information
1986 if (channel_stats.ssl_version_bytes) {
1987 char bytes[5];
1988 snprintf(bytes, sizeof(bytes), "%04X", channel_stats.ssl_version_bytes);
1989 transport_stats->tls_version = bytes;
1990 }
1991 if (channel_stats.ssl_cipher_suite != rtc::TLS_NULL_WITH_NULL_NULL &&
1992 rtc::SSLStreamAdapter::SslCipherSuiteToName(
1993 channel_stats.ssl_cipher_suite)
1994 .length()) {
1995 transport_stats->dtls_cipher =
1996 rtc::SSLStreamAdapter::SslCipherSuiteToName(
1997 channel_stats.ssl_cipher_suite);
1998 }
1999 if (channel_stats.srtp_crypto_suite != rtc::SRTP_INVALID_CRYPTO_SUITE &&
2000 rtc::SrtpCryptoSuiteToName(channel_stats.srtp_crypto_suite)
2001 .length()) {
2002 transport_stats->srtp_cipher =
2003 rtc::SrtpCryptoSuiteToName(channel_stats.srtp_crypto_suite);
2004 }
2005 report->AddStats(std::move(transport_stats));
2006 }
2007 }
2008}

2010std::map<std::string, RTCStatsCollector::CertificateStatsPair>
2011RTCStatsCollector::PrepareTransportCertificateStats_n(
2012 const std::map<std::string, cricket::TransportStats>&
2013 transport_stats_by_name) const {
2014 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
2015 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
2016
2017 std::map<std::string, CertificateStatsPair> transport_cert_stats;
2018 for (const auto& entry : transport_stats_by_name) {
2019 const std::string& transport_name = entry.first;
2020
2021 CertificateStatsPair certificate_stats_pair;
2022 rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate> local_certificate;
2023 if (pc_->GetLocalCertificate(transport_name, &local_certificate)) {
2024 certificate_stats_pair.local =
2025 local_certificate->GetSSLCertificateChain().GetStats();
2026 }
2027
2028 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLCertChain> remote_cert_chain =
2029 pc_->GetRemoteSSLCertChain(transport_name);
2030 if (remote_cert_chain) {
2031 certificate_stats_pair.remote = remote_cert_chain->GetStats();
2032 }
2033
2034 transport_cert_stats.insert(
2035 std::make_pair(transport_name, std::move(certificate_stats_pair)));
2036 }
2037 return transport_cert_stats;
2038}
2039
2040void RTCStatsCollector::PrepareTransceiverStatsInfosAndCallStats_s_w_n() {
2041 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
2042
2043 transceiver_stats_infos_.clear();
2044 // These are used to invoke GetStats for all the media channels together in
2045 // one worker thread hop.
2046 std::map<cricket::VoiceMediaChannel*,
2047 std::unique_ptr<cricket::VoiceMediaInfo>>
2048 voice_stats;
2049 std::map<cricket::VideoMediaChannel*,
2050 std::unique_ptr<cricket::VideoMediaInfo>>
2051 video_stats;
2052
2053 auto transceivers = pc_->GetTransceiversInternal();
2054
2055 // TODO(tommi): See if we can avoid synchronously blocking the signaling
2056 // thread while we do this (or avoid the Invoke at all).
2057 network_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, &transceivers,
2058 &voice_stats, &video_stats] {
2059 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
2060
2061 for (const auto& transceiver_proxy : transceivers) {
2062 RtpTransceiver* transceiver = transceiver_proxy->internal();
2063 cricket::MediaType media_type = transceiver->media_type();
2064
2065 // Prepare stats entry. The TrackMediaInfoMap will be filled in after the
2066 // stats have been fetched on the worker thread.
2067 transceiver_stats_infos_.emplace_back();
2068 RtpTransceiverStatsInfo& stats = transceiver_stats_infos_.back();
2069 stats.transceiver = transceiver;
2070 stats.media_type = media_type;
2071
2072 cricket::ChannelInterface* channel = transceiver->channel();
2073 if (!channel) {
2074 // The remaining fields require a BaseChannel.
2075 continue;
2076 }
2077
2078 stats.mid = channel->content_name();
2079 stats.transport_name = channel->transport_name();
2080
2081 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
2082 auto* voice_channel = static_cast<cricket::VoiceChannel*>(channel);
2083 RTC_DCHECK(voice_stats.find(voice_channel->media_channel()) ==
2084 voice_stats.end());
2085 voice_stats[voice_channel->media_channel()] =
2086 std::make_unique<cricket::VoiceMediaInfo>();
2087 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
2088 auto* video_channel = static_cast<cricket::VideoChannel*>(channel);
2089 RTC_DCHECK(video_stats.find(video_channel->media_channel()) ==
2090 video_stats.end());
2091 video_stats[video_channel->media_channel()] =
2092 std::make_unique<cricket::VideoMediaInfo>();
2093 } else {
2094 RTC_NOTREACHED();
2095 }
2096 }
2097 });
2098
2099 // We jump to the worker thread and call GetStats() on each media channel as
2100 // well as GetCallStats(). At the same time we construct the
2101 // TrackMediaInfoMaps, which also needs info from the worker thread. This
2102 // minimizes the number of thread jumps.
2103 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
2104 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
2105
2106 for (const auto& entry : voice_stats) {
2107 if (!entry.first->GetStats(entry.second.get(),
2108 /*get_and_clear_legacy_stats=*/false)) {
2109 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to get voice stats.";
2110 }
2111 }
2112 for (const auto& entry : video_stats) {
2113 if (!entry.first->GetStats(entry.second.get())) {
2114 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to get video stats.";
2115 }
2116 }
2117
2118 // Create the TrackMediaInfoMap for each transceiver stats object.
2119 for (auto& stats : transceiver_stats_infos_) {
2120 auto transceiver = stats.transceiver;
2121 std::unique_ptr<cricket::VoiceMediaInfo> voice_media_info;
2122 std::unique_ptr<cricket::VideoMediaInfo> video_media_info;
2123 if (transceiver->channel()) {
2124 cricket::MediaType media_type = transceiver->media_type();
2125 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
2126 auto* voice_channel =
2127 static_cast<cricket::VoiceChannel*>(transceiver->channel());
2128 RTC_DCHECK(voice_stats[voice_channel->media_channel()]);
2129 voice_media_info =
2130 std::move(voice_stats[voice_channel->media_channel()]);
2131 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
2132 auto* video_channel =
2133 static_cast<cricket::VideoChannel*>(transceiver->channel());
2134 RTC_DCHECK(video_stats[video_channel->media_channel()]);
2135 video_media_info =
2136 std::move(video_stats[video_channel->media_channel()]);
2137 }
2138 }
2139 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal>> senders;
2140 for (const auto& sender : transceiver->senders()) {
2141 senders.push_back(sender->internal());
2142 }
2143 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInternal>> receivers;
2144 for (const auto& receiver : transceiver->receivers()) {
2145 receivers.push_back(receiver->internal());
2146 }
2147 stats.track_media_info_map = std::make_unique<TrackMediaInfoMap>(
2148 std::move(voice_media_info), std::move(video_media_info), senders,
2149 receivers);
2150 }
2151
2152 call_stats_ = pc_->GetCallStats();
2153 });
2154}
